        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2467083970" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10346983743011302676">A wonderful book set in 20th century India, about family, loss, grief and realisation. Raised by a doting poor aunt and neglected by their parents, Bimla, Tara, Raja and Baba grow up in the backdrop of political conflict, their lives filled with poetry and play. As they grow older and as life drifts them apart, their house in Old Delhi becomes a monument of times past as the main characters Tara and Bimla struggle to bridge past and present while confronting their failures and disappointments. A</span>
  <span id="freeText10346983743011302676" style="display:none">A wonderful book set in 20th century India, about family, loss, grief and realisation. Raised by a doting poor aunt and neglected by their parents, Bimla, Tara, Raja and Baba grow up in the backdrop of political conflict, their lives filled with poetry and play. As they grow older and as life drifts them apart, their house in Old Delhi becomes a monument of times past as the main characters Tara and Bimla struggle to bridge past and present while confronting their failures and disappointments. Although a slow read, especially the first half of the story, it is filled with so many beautiful passages that I loved.</span>
