<span id="freeTextContainer9121190055061297204">This is not, I admit, a mode that I enjoy much anymore -- very serious, lyrical, the uncovering of past tragedies and hurts, lots of interior family dynamics. Never a playful moment, never a wink or a laugh, or even much joy. On the other hand, this book does this mode as well as or better than any I&apos;ve seen, so I have to give the author credit: she knows what she is about. The interest of the book grows, also, over time; layers and layers of complexity are revealed and draw you in just as you t</span>
  <span id="freeText9121190055061297204" style="display:none">This is not, I admit, a mode that I enjoy much anymore -- very serious, lyrical, the uncovering of past tragedies and hurts, lots of interior family dynamics. Never a playful moment, never a wink or a laugh, or even much joy. On the other hand, this book does this mode as well as or better than any I've seen, so I have to give the author credit: she knows what she is about. The interest of the book grows, also, over time; layers and layers of complexity are revealed and draw you in just as you thought the book was simpler than it is. </span>
