  <span id="freeText7540089572147682751" style="display:none">I was disappointed in this book about contemporary Indian life compared one aging sister from America re-visits her Indian family who still sit, numbly in the old, flaking mason and suffer with sighs on the shadowy green lit veranda. I've read a fair bit of wonderful contemporary Indian fiction over the last few years where the characters, plot and descriptions reveal everything to the reader in gorgeous prose and surprising revelations. This, however is not one of them. Nothing really changes from beginning to end except there is more repetition of the existence they all lead now. It's not terrible, just daily cliches.</span>
