<div id="review_4031599842" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4031599842" />
    <a title="Smitha Murthy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3547543-smitha-murthy"><img alt="Smitha Murthy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607182559p2/3547543.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4031599842?book_show_action=true">May 30, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Smitha Murthy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Smitha Murthy" href="/user/show/3547543-smitha-murthy">Smitha Murthy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/25300303-clear-light-of-day">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=strong-women">strong-women</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=india">india</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=relationships">relationships</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=women-writers">women-writers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=family">family</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4031599842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4327390375990547281">What a slow, affecting, intense read this. I picked up ‘Clear Light Of Day’ on the recommendation of Padmaja (Bookishtales). Initially, I was lost in the rich, lush prose and the plot. That’s not Anita Desai’s fault - it’s mine as my mind slowly unravels itself from post-Covid brain fog. But despite that struggle, I was moved by the depth of the story. There’s something to this book I can’t place - during these times, it made me realize even more acutely the largeness of life and love. <br/><br/>With a pa</span>
  <span id="freeText4327390375990547281" style="display:none">What a slow, affecting, intense read this. I picked up ‘Clear Light Of Day’ on the recommendation of Padmaja (Bookishtales). Initially, I was lost in the rich, lush prose and the plot. That’s not Anita Desai’s fault - it’s mine as my mind slowly unravels itself from post-Covid brain fog. But despite that struggle, I was moved by the depth of the story. There’s something to this book I can’t place - during these times, it made me realize even more acutely the largeness of life and love. <br /><br />With a painter’s brush, Desai drew me into a family’s deepest secrets. And no, they don’t involve murder or incest or rape. But they do involve what we all have: a deep search for identity, a sense of abandonment, difficult parenting, choking responsibilities, and a weird love that is not obligation, but the result of years of shared experience. <br /><br />I cried at the end. And considering my morose reading self, that says everything about this book. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4327390375990547281" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
