<span id="freeTextContainer5693855118245216065">I wrote a long review of this book, but it was lost as the result of a stray keystroke that caused it to be deleted and the screen modified. Rather than spend another hour trying to recover my thoughts, I will only say that I loved this book. It is a study of a woman named Bimla Das who opts, instead of going out into the world like two of her siblings, to take care of the members of the family who need the care. It was short-listed for the Booker Prize and, to my view, should have won it. I mus</span>
  <span id="freeText5693855118245216065" style="display:none">I wrote a long review of this book, but it was lost as the result of a stray keystroke that caused it to be deleted and the screen modified. Rather than spend another hour trying to recover my thoughts, I will only say that I loved this book. It is a study of a woman named Bimla Das who opts, instead of going out into the world like two of her siblings, to take care of the members of the family who need the care. It was short-listed for the Booker Prize and, to my view, should have won it. I must read more of her books.</span>
