  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_330336601" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/330336601" />
    <a title="Josephine (Jo)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5918846-josephine-jo"><img alt="Josephine (Jo)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1500813731p2/5918846.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/330336601?book_show_action=true">May 15, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Josephine (Jo)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Josephine (Jo)" href="/user/show/5918846-josephine-jo">Josephine (Jo)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099276180" href="/book/show/275599.Clear_Light_of_Day">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5918846-josephine-jo?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5918846-josephine-jo?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5918846-josephine-jo?shelf=family">family</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5918846-josephine-jo?shelf=india">india</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer330336601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13957798874350899873">I enjoyed this book because it was very different to the type of novel that I usually read. The pace was very slow and the setting was entirely within the confines of the family house in Delhi.<br/>When Tara comes home to visit her family, together with her husband and children, the silence and dust of the years are both disturbed and old memories are stirred. Bim, Tara&apos;s sister, has been left behind both physically and emotionally at the old house, looking after her aunt who drinks and her younger b</span>
  <span id="freeText13957798874350899873" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book because it was very different to the type of novel that I usually read. The pace was very slow and the setting was entirely within the confines of the family house in Delhi.<br />When Tara comes home to visit her family, together with her husband and children, the silence and dust of the years are both disturbed and old memories are stirred. Bim, Tara's sister, has been left behind both physically and emotionally at the old house, looking after her aunt who drinks and her younger brother who has learning difficulties and plays the same few records over and over again on a wind up record player. Tara has an interesting life and their older brother Raja has become rich and no longer shows much interest in what is happening at home in Delhi. The story is set during the time of the partition of India and although I did learn quite a lot from it, it was so subtly included among the hum drum daily life that I was hardly aware of it.<br />The description of the dusty old house and the somewhat neglected garden, with its still sweet scented flowers, was so well done that I could see it, also whilst reading I could feel the horrid overpowering heat, dust and humidity of the Indian summer. I felt so sorry for Bim and wanted to 'set her free' but I am not sure that she would have known how to be free; she had been responsible for everyone else for so long that it had become her entire life. The reader can feel the hopelessness, envy and hurt that is lurking under the surface of her calm exterior. But everyone has a breaking point. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13957798874350899873" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

